message.content:
30 years ago, you were 6 and your sister was half your age, which means she was 3 years old at that time (6 / 2 = 3).

Now, if you are currently 80 years old, we can add the 30 years to find out how old your sister is now:

80 (your current age) - 30 (years ago when she was 3) = 50

So, your sister is 50 years old now.
